Vendored copies of 17 known-ground-truth cosmology datasets from CP3-Origins/Things-to-bench
(gzipped CSVs; upstream commit 69a45dd, fetched 2026-07-10), the dataset companion of cp3-bench:
"cp3-bench: A tool for benchmarking symbolic regression algorithms tested with cosmology",
M. E. Thing & S. M. Koksbang, arXiv:2406.15531.

License: MIT (LICENSE.things-to-bench alongside; Copyright (c) 2023 CP3-Origins). The cp3-bench
tool repo (method wrappers, no data) is separately MIT.

Selection: the known-GT subset only — C1a-C1d (LCDM H(z)), C2a-C2b (redshift drift), C3g-C3h
(two-region backreaction, the two C3 members WITH a closed form), C5a-C5f (NFW/Burkert halo
profiles), C6a-C6c (gravitational-wave-inspired h_plus toys). The GT-free discovery sets
(C3a-C3f, C4a-C4e) and the F1-F8 GP-toy re-renderings (dedup to our existing DSO-derived suites)
are intentionally NOT vendored; the F-set dedup and three upstream paper-vs-data discrepancies
(C3h sign/prefactor, C6a phase, C6c m2=m1) are documented in the catalog build report.

These files are the build input for the `cp3-cosmo` catalog (tools/build_cp3_cosmo.py).
